- `isWignerMatrix`: This defines the structure of a Wigner matrix, including the probability measures μ and ν for the diagonal and off-diagonal entries, respectively. It also defines the matrix as a function from `Fin n × Fin n` to `ℝ`, with the property that the matrix is symmetric.
- `wignerMatrixMap`: This maps a function from `Index n` (which represents the upper triangle of the matrix indices) to `ℝ` into an `n × n` matrix. The function uses the symmetry property to define the entire matrix.
- `wignerMatrixMeasure`: This defines the probability measure on the space of `n × n` matrices, which is the pushforward of the measure on the space of functions from `Index n` to `ℝ`.
- `wignerMatrixTracePower`: This defines the function that takes a Wigner matrix and returns the trace of its kth power.

